# File: tests/e2e/user-views-notice-cards.spec.sh.ab
# Purpose: Verify notice and important notice cards span all 3 grid columns at full width on desktop, render normally on mobile, and dismiss correctly
# Dependencies: [app/app/post/notice/notice.directive.js.ab, app/app/post/importantNotice/importantNotice.directive.js.ab, app/assets/scss/_feed-grid.scss.ab, app/app/post/post.directive.js.ab]

## Overview
An authenticated user views the listing feed on desktop and sees system notice and important notice cards spanning the full width of the 3-column grid. The notices preserve their content and readability. On mobile, the full-width class has no visual effect. Dismissing an important notice reflows the grid correctly.

## Covers
app/app/post/notice/notice.directive.js.ab, app/app/post/importantNotice/importantNotice.directive.js.ab, app/assets/scss/_feed-grid.scss.ab, app/app/post/post.directive.js.ab

## Business Actor
Authenticated user viewing the listing feed where system notices or important notices are present.

## Business Goal
See announcement and notice cards clearly spanning the full feed width on desktop, with correct display on mobile, and the ability to dismiss important notices.

## Test Accounts
<!-- Credentials are defined here and used verbatim by the translator. Do NOT read from .env or any external file. -->
<!-- Each actor gets a base email. At runtime the translator appends +<random_id> to make it unique per run. -->
- Actor `user`: base email `e2e.noticeuser@test.local`, password `Test1234!`

## Preconditions
- Each run creates a fresh isolated account using `e2e.noticeuser+<random_id>@test.local` via the registration API before Scenario A runs. This account is fully isolated — no shared state with other specs or runs.
- The test environment contains at least one system notice and at least one important notice in the feed (read-only seed data or admin-created fixtures).
- The test environment contains at least 3 donation listings interspersed with the notices.
- Desktop viewport is set above 768px (e.g., 1280x800).

Teardown (after all scenarios, even on failure):
- Delete the per-run account created during setup and all records it owns.
- Do NOT delete shared read-only seed fixtures (notices and listings).

## Business Scenarios
- Scenario A (DB-1): Desktop — notice card spans all 3 columns at full width
- Scenario B (DB-2): Mobile — notice card renders normally in single-column (no regression)
- Scenario C (DB-3): Desktop — important notice dismissed via 'Entendido' button, grid reflows

## Actor Variants
- EQ-1 — Desktop feed with a notice-type card among donation cards -> DB-1
- EQ-2 — Desktop feed with an importantNotice-type card at the top of the feed -> DB-1
- EQ-3 — Desktop feed with both notice and donation cards interspersed -> DB-1
- EQ-4 — Mobile viewport with a notice card present -> DB-2

## Outcome Branches
- DB-1 -> Notice card with feed-grid-full-width class spans all 3 columns, full width, layout and readability preserved (EQ-1, EQ-2, EQ-3)
- DB-2 -> Mobile: notice card displays at 100% column width, single-column layout unchanged (EQ-4)
- DB-3 -> Important notice dismissed, card removed from DOM, grid reflows normally

## Business Boundaries
- BV-1 (notice content volume, minimal): short-text notice still spans full width
- BV-2 (notice content volume, rich): long-text notice with embedded HTML and action buttons preserves readability at full grid width

## Acceptance Criteria
- AC1: On desktop, notice cards span all 3 columns at full width with layout and readability preserved (DB-1, EQ-1, EQ-2, EQ-3)
- AC2: On desktop, important notice cards also span all 3 columns at full width (DB-1, EQ-2)
- AC3: Notice and donation cards can be interspersed in the same feed — donations fill 3-column rows, notices span full width (DB-1, EQ-3)
- AC4: On mobile, notice cards display at full column width in single-column layout with no regression (DB-2, EQ-4)
- AC5: A minimal-content notice still spans the full 3-column width (BV-1)
- AC6: A rich-content notice with long text preserves readability at full grid width (BV-2)
- AC7: After dismissing an important notice via 'Entendido', the card is removed and the grid reflows without leaving a gap (DB-3)
- AC8: No notice card renders at only one column width on desktop (ABSENT-1)
- AC9: No notice card is wider than the viewport on mobile (ABSENT-2)

## Absent Elements
- When notice card is visible on desktop: no partial-width rendering — notice does not occupy only one grid column
- When notice card is visible on mobile: no layout regression — card displays at 100% column width, not wider than viewport

## Steps

### Scenario A: Notice cards span full width on desktop
<!-- covers: DB-1, EQ-1, EQ-2, EQ-3, BV-1, BV-2, ABSENT-1 -->
1. Log in as the test user on a desktop viewport (1280x800)
2. Navigate to the listing feed at $E2E_BASE_URL
3. Wait for the feed to load with donation cards and notice cards visible
4. Locate a system notice card in the feed
5. Verify AC1: the notice card visually spans the full width of the 3-column grid (all 3 columns)
6. Verify Absent: the notice is not rendered at a single-column width
7. Verify the notice content (text, any embedded HTML) is readable at this full width
8. Locate an important notice card (if visible at the top of the feed)
9. Verify AC2: the important notice also spans all 3 columns at full width
10. Verify AC3: donation cards around the notices are arranged in the normal 3-column grid
11. Verify AC5: a short-text notice spans full width (BV-1)
12. If a rich-content notice with long text or HTML is present, verify AC6: readability is preserved (BV-2)
13. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/notice-cards/desktop-full-width.png

### Scenario B: Notice cards on mobile — no regression
<!-- covers: DB-2, EQ-4, ABSENT-2 -->
1. Resize viewport to mobile width (375x812)
2. Verify AC4: notice cards display at full column width in single-column layout
3. Verify Absent: no notice card is wider than the viewport — no horizontal scrollbar
4. Verify the mobile layout is identical to pre-grid behavior
5. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/notice-cards/mobile-notice.png

### Scenario C: Important notice dismissed — grid reflows
<!-- covers: DB-3 -->
1. Resize viewport back to desktop width (1280x800)
2. Locate an important notice card in the feed
3. Click the 'Entendido' (dismiss) button on the important notice
4. Verify AC7: the important notice card is removed from the feed
5. Verify the remaining cards reflow in the grid without leaving a gap where the notice was
6. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/notice-cards/notice-dismissed.png

